<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN209">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>poykai nārai pōrviṟ cēkku</l>
<l>neytalaṅ kaḻaṉi nellari toḻuvar</l>
<l>kūmpuviṭu meṉpiṇi yaviḻnta vāmpa</l>
<l>lakalaṭai yariyaṉ māntit teṇkaṭaṟ</l>
<l>paṭutirai yiṉcīrp pāṇi tūṅku</l>
<l>meṉpulam vaippi ṉaṉṉāṭṭup poruna</l>
<l>palkaṉi nacaii yalkuvicum pukantu</l>
<l>perumalai viṭarakañ cilampa muṉṉip</l>
<l>paḻaṉuṭaip perumaran tīrnteṉak kaiyaṟṟup</l>
<l>peṟātu peyarum puḷḷiṉam pōlaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉacaitara vantuniṉ ṉicainuval paricilēṉ</l>
<l>vaṟuviyēṉ peyarkō vāṇmēm paṭuna</l>
<l>vīyā yāyiṉu miraṅkuve ṉallē</l>
<l>ṉōyilai yākumati peruma nammuṭ</l>
<l>kuṟunaṇi kāṇkuva tāka nāḷu</l>
<l>naṟumpa lolivaruṅ katuppiṉ ṭēmoḻit</l>
<l>teriyiḻai makaḷir pāṇi pārkkum</l>
<l>peruvarai yaṉṉa mārpiṟ</l>
<l>ceruveñ cēeyniṉ makiḻiruk kaiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O fighter of a good land in the region of soft soil, (6)</l>
<l>where the paddy-cutting workmen in the paddy fields with blue waterlilies (2)</l>
<l>on heaps of which the herons from the pond rest, (1)</l>
<l>feed on toddy from the wide leaves (4a-c)</l>
<l>of white waterlilies that opened [their] soft outer petals to release the closed [buds] (3)</l>
<l>[and] sway to the pleasing measured rhythm of the clear sea’s dashing waves, (4d-5) </l>
<l>like a flock of birds that, (10cd)</l>
<l>yearning for many ripe fruit, ascend the sky where they stay, (7)</l>
<l>approach a big mountain so that the inside of caves resound, (8)</l>
<l>are prostrate because the big tree that had fruit had coe to an end, (9)</l>
<l>  [and] return without having obtained [anything], (10ab)</l>
<l>having come yearning for you, shall I, a gift-seeker uttering your fame (11)</l>
<l>return a poor man? O you who excel with the sword (12)</l>
<l>even if you won’t give I will not lament. (13)</l>
<l>Be without pain, great man. Among us, (14)</l>
<l>it being seen in near proximity, (15a-c)</l>
<l>there is the delightful seat of you, [like] the Red one, hot in fight, (19)</l>
<l>with a chest like a big mountain, (18)</l>
<l>for whose beat women with clear jewels look, (17)</l>
<l>with sweet words, [their] hair sprouting in many fragrant [curls], (16)</l>
<l>daily. (15d)   </l>
</lg>
